 <name>rdump</name>
 <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
 <summary>Capture a PHP process's own memory for offline analysis with reli (finding leaks, reference cycles, memory bottlenecks, etc.).</summary>
 <description>
Writes a snapshot of the current PHP process's own memory to a file, which
reli (reliforp/reli-prof) analyses offline to inspect the call stack and
per-object memory and to find leaks, reference cycles and memory bottlenecks.
Linux only.
 </description>
